\n<Constance>Radro is really good at cooking! She praises me a lot
if I eat everything, but I can't leave any even if I wanted
to because it's so delicious!

\n<Constance>But then, Samuel starts teasing me saying, "You'll get fat,"
and it always turns into a fight. I don't even want to
fight!
\n<Aventus>...

\n<Samuel>Dig dig dig... If I dig a hole here, some really gross bugs
come out. I'll show them to you when they do.

\n<Fair>I'm the oldest one here! That means I'm the most important!
Second only to Lady Radlo! Show some respect!

\n<Fair>Ah, but I read in a book that important people don't say
they're important themselves! I'm not saying I'm important,
but I am the oldest! I'm really not important! It's true!
\n<Francois>You know, I actually think that Radro mama is pretty cute!

\n<Francois>Hey, this is a secret, alright! Don't you dare tell anyone
else! If you do, I'll pinch you!

\n<Roar>I want to become a scholar. If I can solve even one of the
10,000 mysteries of this world, then it's my victory!

\n<Roar>Some people say this place isn't suited for studying, but
there must be things that can only be learned here. I'll
show them that one's birth and upbringing have nothing to do
with scholarship!

\n<Grandpa>Staying in the noble district means a lot of climbing up and
down. It's quite harsh on an old body like mine.

\n<Grandpa>The head of the family is furious. If they find out I've
been turning a blind eye, I might lose my head. Please plead
on my behalf if that happens.

\n<Grandpa>Right now, everyone in the mansion is searching for the two
of you. Well, they'd never imagine you're in Drine, so
there's no worry of being found.

\n<Grandpa>How did I know you were here? Well, as your tutor, I can see
right through your thoughts.

\n<Grandpa>But my body can't keep up anymore... It took quite some time
to get here. It was about a six-day journey by carriage,
with plenty of rests.

\n<Grandpa>\n[8], did you really get here in one night? No matter how
high your physical abilities and the blessing of the wind...
Goodness. You're practically a monster.

\n<Grandpa>It seems beastfolk are rare around here. I've only seen an
elderly tanuki. I'm an old dog myself.

\n<Grandpa>I should have dressed more shabbily. The residents of the
slums are giving me some intense stares.

\n<Grandpa>I'm well-versed in self-defense, so it's no problem if I'm
attacked. Still spry in my old age. Just a bit of joint
pain, though.

\n<Grandpa>I won't enter the Adventurer's Guild. It would be
troublesome if your identities were questioned. I'll just
loiter around here.

\n<Grandpa>That vase was a gift from the head of the family two
generations ago. We were close in age, and he treated me
like a friend... He was as cheerful as Miss Chelsea.

\n<Grandpa>That \n[8] broke it might have been some kind of divine
revelation. I take it as a message from the previous head of
the family.

\n<Grandpa>\n[8] uses "Cat's Paw" in combat, but originally it was
meant to assist with writing documents and such. It's a
magic used by the executive branch.

\n<Grandpa>There's a saying, "even a cat's hand is desired," right?
That's where it comes from. It's a magic with quite an
honorable history.

\n<Grandpa>I am watching over your growth, but since you left home on
your own, I won't lend a hand. My hands, that is.

\n<Grandpa>By the way... \n[8], you are still in the midst of growing
up. I hope you make the right choices.\C[1] (Current Karma
Value 0)

\n<Grandpa>By the way... since coming here, it seems \n[8] has grown.
This old man is a bit relieved.\C[1] (Current Karma Value
\v[270])

\n<Grandpa>By the way... \n[8], you seem to have changed somehow.
Don't do anything too reckless.\C[14] (Current Karma Value
\v[270])

\n<Female>"The name of this town is 'Dri-Ne'. It means 'sinkhole'. A
hole that suddenly appeared due to the ground collapsing.
That's how this town came to be."

\n<Female>"Above this town live the upper class, and us commoners like
me live off the scraps they throw away."

\n<Female>"This is where those who have lost their way end up,
swallowed up like into a drain. All sorts of schemes and
desires swirl around here."
\n<Dirty Dog>*pant*...*pant*...*pant*...

\n<Annie>\n[1]! The town is in chaos! We've evacuated everyone who
can't fight! But there are monsters in the residential area
too...! Damn it! Why is this happening all of a sudden!!

parameters: \n<The Demon Lord's Aide>Eh-...Welcome. To the Demon Lord's castle, humans.
\n<Grandpa>Wha, Demon Lord's castle...!? What do you mean!?

\n<Seibel>Eh...? It's just a forest. There's just a chair placed in
the forest. Eh? Demon Lord?
1テラ困惑
\n<Terra>Um... Demon Lord? What is all this...

\n<The Demon Lord>You know... you all were about to be buried alive. Do you
understand that... ugh... uweehh!! I feel like vomiting...

\n<The Demon Lord's Aide>By the Demon Lord's ingenious arrangement, you were all
invited to the Demon Lord's castle via a wide-range
teleport. Isn't that right?

\n<The Demon Lord>No, that's not it... Look here... *sigh*... *sigh*... You
wouldn't understand...

\n<The Demon Lord>To me, demons are like... umm. Bottle ships. You get it? Do
you know what a bottle ship is?

\n<The Demon Lord>You know, using toothpicks and tweezers to make an intricate
model ship inside a bottle. That's what I'm talking about.
*cough*!

\n<The Demon Lord>It's a work of art. Extremely delicate. Especially the
higher-ups. Well, imps and such are fine even if they get
crushed.

\n<The Demon Lord>Every single day, gluing tiny parts together, meticulously,
meticulously, inserting tweezers into the bottle, and if
even one part is wrong, it's all over.

\n<The Demon Lord>It's not sane, right? And when it's finally complete. Have
you ever thought about how it feels to have it destroyed?

\n<The Demon Lord>It's beyond just flipping out. To me, demons are bottle
ships. How about that. It got through to you clearly, didn't
it. Ugh, uweh...

\n<Aide>As expected of you. An extremely easy-to-understand analogy.
Even a low-intelligence Warbear would have understood.
1テラ困惑

\n<Terra>So, in other words... you teleported us over a wide area to
save us, and humans came along too, is that correct?

\n<The Demon Lord>I only knew the approximate location. Thanks to that, I've
been feeling dizzy and nauseous since earlier... *cough*!
I'm running out of magical power.

\n<The Demon Lord>Wait a minute... let me rest. Don't move, any of you...
*cough*! *cough*!
1ラティエ困惑

\n<Bijou>(I only remember up until the guild was blown away. If I
knew this would happen, I should have escaped sooner... My
drunkenness has completely sobered up.)

\n<Guild Master>(Is that the Demon Lord? Damn it. Can't see from here. He
sure talks a lot.)

\n<Grandpa>(The young master and young lady seem to be safe as well...
But why are they on that side...?)
\n<The Demon Lord>Phew... I'm starting to feel a bit better. So tired...

\n<The Demon Lord>So, what I'm trying to say is this. What's done is done.
Humans. All of you are going to be killed.

\n<The Demon Lord>But that's not a constructive conversation. Rather, it's not
interesting. This must be some kind of fate.

\n<The Demon Lord>Humans are ugly creatures. You humans were almost killed by
other humans. Judging from the coagulation crystal matter,
it was planned from the start.

\n<The Demon Lord>Using the coagulation crystal to lure demons and attack the
slums. Then burying everyone alive to catch them all in one
fell swoop. Anyone here have an idea who might be
responsible?

\n<Guild Master>Ah... yes, there's no doubt about it. What the Demon Lord is
saying is correct. It was orchestrated by Count Noblesse.
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>... (It's my fault for stealing it. Even if I was forced to
steal, it's... my fault that everyone got involved.)
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>... (It's my fault for stealing it. Even if I was forced to
steal, it's... my fault that everyone got involved.)

\n<The Demon Lord>Such a plan couldn't have been concocted overnight. There
must have been meticulous preparation. Gunpowder, sorcerers,
barrier technicians. Could they really gather all that in
such a short time?

\n<The Demon Lord>If things had continued as they were, you all would have
been buried alive by those above. In other words, I'm your
lifesaver. Isn't that right?

\n<The Demon Lord>Your lives were picked up by me. It's only logical to use
them for my sake. You were about to be killed by humans.
Become my subordinates and let's take revenge on the humans.

\n<Dodon>T-true... Unforgivable. They tried to kill us... all the
people in the slums.

\n<Seibel>We were certainly a thorn in their side. Or should I say
under their eyes? But being buried alive... that's too much.

\n<Innkeeper Granny>Those scumbags above. They even tried to bury this old
woman. They could at least wait until I die.
\n<Guild Master>I feel like my guts are boiling. That bastard...

\n<Rintei>No, you're wrong! If the demons hadn't attacked, those above
wouldn't have done such a thing!

\n<Rintei>You mustn't listen to what the Demon Lord says! We are
humans! Humans shouldn't harbor hatred towards each other!
Demons are meant to lead people astray...
\n<Rakura>Rintei!!

\n<The Demon Lord>Don't get the choices mixed up. I'm not talking about
whether to side with humans or demons. The choice is whether
to become my subordinate or die right now.
\n<Rintei>It's... okay. It's not a fatal wound... not yet...

\n<Aide>No, it's definitely a fatal wound. Your guts are spilling
out.

\n<Annie>O-okay! I'll do as you say! But please heal Rintei! I beg
you!

\n<The Demon Lord>Fine. Well, that's okay then. You must obey every command.
If you do, I'll at least guarantee your lives.
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>Please, Demon Lord-sama. I don't care what happens to me.
But please, spare the children.

\n<The Demon Lord>I'm not talking about forgiving or not forgiving. Seriously,
humans just don't listen. Fine! Whatever! It's so annoying!
Do as you like!
1ラドロP照れ2

\n<Radro>... (Ah, as soon as I felt relieved, suddenly the strength
is... I feel dizzy...)
1ラドロP照れ

\n<Bijou>(I see. How interesting. If it means my life is saved, I
don't care which side I'm on.)

\n<The Demon Lord>Hey! Demons! If you eat these guys without my permission,
I'll kill you! Got it? Those who try to escape can be eaten!

\n<The Demon Lord>For now, make these guys build a house or something. Keep a
close watch on them. That's all! Dismissed! Succubi, stay
behind!
